items.title: Judge bashes 42nd, ties mark at home park
items.summary: Yankees phenom Aaron Judge hit his 42nd home run of the season Thursday night. It was his 26th homer at new Yankee Stadium, which ties Curtis Granderson's

items.title: Astros' Fiers handed 5-game suspension
items.summary: Astros pitcher Mike Fiers has received a five-game suspension and an undisclosed fine for intentionally throwing a pitch in the area of the head of Luis Valbuena of the Angels in the bottom of the fourth inning of Wednesday evening's game at Angel Stadium.
